            "1 Public Enterprises Survey 2024-25\nExecutive Summary\nThe Public Enterprises Survey\nThe Public Enterprises Survey 2024-25 presents a summary of the financial performance of Central Public\nSector Enterprises for the Financial Year 2024-25. The Section 2 (45) of Companies Act, 2013 defines\nGovernment Company to mean – any company in which not less than 51 percent of the paid-up share capital\nis held by Central Government, or by any State Government or Governments, or partly by the Central\nGovernment and partly by one or more State Governments and includes a company which is a subsidiary\ncompany of such a Government Company.\nCoverage\nThe Public Enterprises Survey traditionally covers, besides certain statutory corporations, those\nGovernment companies wherein more than 50% equity is held by the Central Government. The subsidiaries\nof these companies, if registered in India, where any CPSE has more than 50% equity are also categorised as\nCPSEs. The survey does not cover departmentally run public enterprises, banking institutions and\ninsurance companies. The Public Enterprises Survey 2024-25 is the 65th publication in this series. The\nsurvey presents the picture of 475 CPSEs which includes 291 Operating CPSEs.\nKey Highlights:\nThe survey provides essential statistical data for all CPSEs from various perspectives by segregating these\nenterprises into various sectors such as Agriculture, Mining & Exploration, Manufacturing, Processing &\nGeneration and Services. The Sector are further divided into Cognates, which are 20 in number.\nHighlights of the Public Enterprises Survey 2024-25 is as follows:"
