            "Public Enterprises Survey 2024-25 Public Enterprises Survey 2024-25 2\n4 Total Gross Revenue from the operations of operating CPSEs during FY 2024-25 was ₹37.01 lakh crore\nas against ₹36.09 lakh crore in FY 2023-24, showing an increase of 2.6%.\n= Among the sectors, Manufacturing, Processing & Generation sector continues to command the\nhighest share which contributed 70.1% to the Gross Revenue in FY 2024-25\n= The four cognate groups - Petroleum (Refinery & Marketing)(54.5%), Power Generation(6.4%),\nTrading & Marketing(5.5%) and Transport and Logistic Services(5.4%) account for 71.8% of the\nGross Revenue in FY 2024-25\n= Top five CPSEs having highest Revenue during FY 2024-25 are Indian Oil Corporation Ltd., Bharat\nPetroleum Corporation Ltd., Hindustan Petroleum Corporation Ltd., Food Corporation of India and\nNTPC Ltd.\n4 Net Profit of profit-making CPSEs stood at ₹3.09 lakh crore in FY 2024-25 against ₹3.43 lakh crore in FY\n2023-24 showing a decrease of 10.1%. The decrease in Net Profit is mainly attributable to the CPSE in\nPetroleum (Refinery and Marketing) Cognate. Top five CPSEs with highest Net profits are Oil & Natural\nGas Corporation Ltd., NTPC Ltd., Power Finance Corporation Ltd., Coal India Ltd. and REC Ltd.\n4 Net Loss of loss-incurring CPSEs was ₹0.18 lakh crore in FY 2024-25 as against ₹0.21 lakh crore in FY\n2023-24 showing a decrease of 13.8%. Major loss incurring CPSEs are ONGC Petro Additions Ltd.,\nMahanagar Telephone Nigam Ltd., NMDC Steel Ltd., Bharat Sanchar Nigam Ltd. and Bharat Petro\nResources Ltd.\n4 Bharat Sanchar Nigam Ltd was able to reduce the loss from ₹5,371 crore in FY 2023-24 to ₹2,247 crores\nin FY 2024-25 and Rashtriya Ispat Nigam Ltd.was able to reduce the loss from ₹4,849 Crore in FY 2023-\n24 to ₹1,389 Crore in FY 2024-25. While NMDC Steel Ltd loss has widened from ₹1,560 crore in FY\n2023-24 to ₹2,374 crores in FY 2024-25.\nPerformance Highlights of CPSE on Select Parameters (₹ Lakh Crores)",
