            "155 Public Enterprises Survey 2024-25\n7.3 Procurement through GeM\nGeM, hosted by Directorate General of Supplies & Disposals (DGS&D) is a paperless, cashless, & system-\ndriven e-market place that enables procurement of common-use goods & services with minimal human\ninterface. It is a dynamic, self-sustaining & user- friendly portal for procurement by offices of various\nGovernment Ministries & Departments, CPSEs & autonomous bodies of the Central Government.\nDGS&D developed GeM with technical support of National e-Governance Division (Ministry of\nElectronics & Information Technology). Intended benefits of the portal are listed below:\nI. Transparency: GeM eliminates human interface in vendor registration, order placement, &\npayment processing to a great extent. Being an open platform, it offers no entry barriers to bona fide\nsuppliers who wish to conduct business with the Government. At every step SMS & e-mail\nnotifications are sent to the buyers, the heads of their organisations, paying authorities & sellers.\nII. Efficiency: Direct purchase on GeM can be done within minutes and the entire process is online &\nend-to-end integrated with online tools for assessing price reasonability. For procurement of higher-\nvalue products & services, a transparent & efficient bidding / Reverse Auction (RA) facility is\navailable on GeM. For creating a bid / RA, buyers do not need to enter their own technical\nspecifications as they have been standardised on GeM. The bid / RA can be created expeditiously &\nfinalised within minimum of seven days.\nIII. Security & Safety: GeM is a secure platform & all the documents on the portal are e-signed at\nvarious stages by buyers & sellers. The antecedents of suppliers are verified online & automatically\nthrough MCA21, Aadhaar & PAN databases. Furthermore, third-party assessment of suppliers is\nconducted by Securities & Exchange Board of India-empanelled credit rating agencies.\nIV. Savings: The transparency, efficiency & ease of use of GeM has resulted in a substantial reduction in\nprices on the portal compared with the tender, rate contract & direct purchase rates. Average prices\non GeM are lower by at least 15-20% & insome cases even up to 56%. GeM also carries out demand\naggregation for items to be procured by various Central/State Government departments.\nV. Inclusivity in the Business Value Chain: Prosperity of the MSE sector is crucial for the growth of\nour country. The sector fuels the economy by providing employment & income to millions of people\nwho work for small, local businesses as well as in start-ups. GeM expects to improve the ease of\ndoing business for such small & medium enterprises and provide inclusivity by giving them a fair &\ntransparent platform to participate in business activities generated from Government sources.\nThe cognate group wise data showing total procurement, annual procurement through GeM & annual\nprocurement from MSEs through GeM during FY 2024-25 is summarised in Table 7.4."
