            "399 Public Enterprises Survey 2024-25\nAppendix - X\nGlossary of Certain Terms Used in This Report\n1. Capital Employed means total shareholder‘s funds and long term borrowings.\n2. Shareholder Funds consists of Paid-up Capital, reserves & surplus (other equity in case of Ind-AS\ncompanies), money received against share warrants and share application money pending allotment.\n3. Financial Investment means Paid-up Capital, share application money pending allotment, money\nreceived against share warrants and long term borrowings.\n4. Gross Block represents original cost of procuring and erecting fixed assets (tangible and intangible)\nas appearing in the annual accounts of the CPSEs at the end of the accounting year and takes into\naccount additions thereto and deduction there from by way of sales and transfers and capital work-in\nprogress and intangible assets under development.\n5. Gross Turnover or Gross Revenue means the revenue from operations including sale of products\n(interest income in case of Financial Enterprises), sale of services and other operating revenue\n(revenue from other financial services in case of financial enterprises) and includes excise duty.\n6. Net Worth means Paid-up Capital, money received against share warrants and all reserves created\nout of the profits and securities premium account excluding reserves created out of revaluation of\nassets, write-back of depreciation & amalgamation less accumulated losses, deferred expenditure and\nmiscellaneous expenditure not written off.\n7. Value Addition consists of profit before tax (PBT), interest, salaries and wages, rent/ royalty and\ncess, depreciation, depletion & amortization, DRE/ impairment.\n8. Operating Margin means Profit before Interest, Exceptional, Extraordinary Items and Tax (PBIEET)\ndivided by Gross Revenue or Turnover."
